==English==
===Noun===
'''tinsel''' (''[[uncountable]]'')

#Very thin strips of a [[glitter]]ing, [[mettalic]] material used as a [[decoration]]; especially in [[Britain]] where, traditionally, at [[Christmas]] time it is [[drape]]d over [[streamer]]s, [[paper chain]]s and the branches of [[Christmas tree]]s.
===Transitive verb===
'''tinsel'''
#To decorate with tinsel.
#(''metaphorical'') To give something a false [[sparkle]].
